djb@silverton.berkeley.edu (D. J. Bernstein) writes:
> The PEM model of key ``certification'' allows one man, Jim Bidzos, to 
> singlehandedly destroy the entire PEM communications system in a matter 
> of days. What were you saying about confidence? 

Nothing in the PEM model requires the use of a single CA.  If you don't trust 
RSA, setup your own CA and convince people to trust you instead.

Or don't use certificates at all and run into the PGP problem.  TANSTAAFL.


